{"word":"H535 - אָמַל - ʼâmal - aw-mal' - Languish","slug":"H535","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אָמַל</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼâmal"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>aw-mal'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Languish"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D0;&#x05DE;&#x05DC; - 'a&#x0302;mal</b> - <i>aw-mal'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>droop</i>; by implication to <i>be sick</i>, to <i>mourn: - </i>languish, be weak, wax feeble."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H536\">H536</a>, <a href=\"#/H537\">H537</a>"}]}